Obtaining an API Key from WeatherAPI.com
Sign Up:
Go to WeatherAPI.com and sign up for an account.

Get API Key:
Once logged in, navigate to the API section and obtain your API key.

Endpoint: /weather
Method: GET
Functionality: Returns the current weather information for a given city.
Request Format

URL: http://api.weatherapi.com/v1/current.json

Method: GET

Parameters:
city (required): Name of the city for which weather information is requested.

Example Request:
GET /weather?city=London

Response Format
Success (200 OK):
{
  "city": "London",
  "temperature": 15.0,
  "condition": "Partly cloudy",
  "humidity": 80,
  "wind_speed": 10.5
}
Error (400 Bad Request)
{
  "error": "City parameter is required"
}
Error (404 Not Found):
{
  "error": "City not found or WeatherAPI.com error",
  "details": "Detailed error message from the request exception"
}

Install Python and Flask:
Ensure you have Python and Flask installed. If not, you can install Flask using pip:
pip install Flask requests

Save the Script:
Save as you go.

Run the Server:
Run the Flask server by executing the script:
python3 api.py

Access the API:
I opened my browser to access the API at (i.e. http://127.0.0.1:5000/weather?city=Atlanta). In addition, I used the curl method. #City name must be entered or else an error message will display.


